        {
          "description": "M2S Problem 1.1 Description",
          "ordinal": 1,
          "title": "Getting Started in M2Studio",
          "subtitle": "",
          "disabled": [],
          "sections": [
            {
              "type": "help",
              "content": {
                "tiles": [
                  {
                    "content": {
                      "type": "Text",
                      "format": "html",
                      "text": [
                        "<p><strong>Welcome to your work space! In here, you will find information and questions. You will work both individually and in groups, so be sure to listen to your teacher about what to do when. </strong></p>",
                        "<p><strong></strong></p>",
                        "<p><strong>Some tips for this workspace:</strong></p>",
                        "<p>To the left, you can see buttons. These will add tiles to this workspace. </p>",
                        "<ul><li>The top button will create a space for you to create a diagram</li><li>The next button (with the A) will create a space for you to write down your thoughts</li><li>The button with the pencil will create a space where you can draw</li></ul>",
                        "<p>You can rearrange your spaces by clicking on the top right-hand corner of the tile (where you will see 6 dots). This will allow you drag and move the tiles. </p>",
                        "<p>You can click on the bottom of a tile and then drag the size up or down to make it smaller or bigger. </p>",
                        "<p>You can share your work with your group-mates by clicking the {???}.</p>",
                        "<p>You can also look at the work of your group-mates by {????}. See something creative that you want to build upon? Drag their tile into your workspace, write &quot;Borrowed from {name}&quot; at the top of the tile, and then make your modifications!</p>",
                        "<p></p>",
                        "<p><strong>Are you ready? Let&#x27;s go!</strong></p>"
                      ]
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "display": "teacher",
                    "content": {
                      "type": "Text",
                      "format": "html",
                      "text": [
                        "<p><strong>Welcome to teacher solutions</strong></p>",
                        "<p><strong>Some tips for this workspace:</strong></p>",
                        "<p>If your students are having trouble, consider putting some tips in a document of your own and publishing it with the uparrow button near the File menu. This will appear in Class Work and students can see the examples you post. They can publish too and the class can share ideas.</p>",
                        "<p>All content from the left hand panels can be dragged into working documents on the right. Some curriculum pieces are intended to be dragged in as starting places for student work.</p>",
                        "<p></p>",
                        "<p><strong>Are you ready? Let&#x27;s go!</strong></p>"
                      ]
                    }
                  }             
                ]
              },
              "supports": []
            },
            {
              "type": "taska",
              "content": {
                "tiles": [
                  {
                    "content": {
                      "type": "Text",
                      "format": "html",
                      "text": [
                        "<p><strong>Situation A</strong></p>",
                        "<p></p>",
                        "<p><strong>The school board wonders how long the school building should be open every day. If they close the building they can save money on operating costs, but then students might not have a place to study. The school board hires you to figure out how long each day the school should be open. Your first task is to determine what percentage of the day students typically spend at school. </strong></p>"
                      ]
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "content": {
                      "type": "Text",
                      "format": "html",
                      "text": [
                        "<p>1. Describe your first task in your own words:</p>",
                        "<p></p>",
                        "<p><em>{Write you answer here}  </em></p>"
                      ]
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "content": {
                      "type": "Text",
                      "format": "html",
                      "text": [
                        "<p>2a. What do you need to know about the school in order to help the board? List as many factors (key quantities and variables) as you can:</p>",
                        "<p></p>",
                        "<p><em>{Write you answer here}  </em></p>",
                        "<p>2b. Next to each factor above, write where you can find out the information or what you would need to do to figure it out. \nExamples:</p>", 
                        "<p>- I need to know know how many pets the students have. --> I will conduct a survey to collect this information. </p>",
                        "<p>- I wonder how many books are at the library. --> Ask the librarian if they have this on record. </p>",
                        "<p><em>{Write you answer here}  </em></p>",
                        "<p>2c. Bonus: Use the [v=] button to formally make the variables in line above. </p>"
                      ]
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "content": {
                      "type": "Text",
                      "format": "html",
                      "text": [
                        "<p>3. What assumptions can you make about the context or factors to help you complete this task?</p>",
                        "<p>Example: By saying 'typical day', the school board likely means to consider only days that school is in session. </p>",
                        "<p>Example: We probably only care about the pets owned by the students on the soccer team. </p>",
                        "<p></p>",
                        "<p><em>{Write you answer here}  </em></p>"
                      ]
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "content": {
                      "type": "Text",
                      "format": "html",
                      "text": [
                        "<p> 4. Select 2 of the factors and explain how/why they are important for helping you to complete the task. Note: You can use the [v=] button to get a list and then select from 'Reference existing variable' to get you started!</p>",
                        "<p>Example: We need to know the number of [pets] so that we buy enough pet food.</p>",
                        "<p></p>",
                        "<p><em>{Write you answer here}  </em></p>"
                      ]
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "content": {
                      "type": "Text",
                      "format": "html",
                      "text": [
                        "<p> 5. Describe in words how some of these factors are related.</p>","<p>Example: The more [pets] we allow in the library, the more [books in the library] will be ripped up.</p>",
                        "<p></p>",
                        "<p><em>{Write you answer here}  </em></p>"
                      ]
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "content": {
                      "type": "Text",
                      "format": "html",
                      "text": [
                        "<p> 6. Use mathematical language to describe the relationship between at least two variables, or create a formula, or sketch a graph. Note; If you want to sketch, click on the pencil in the left panel to create a drawing tile!</p>",
                        "<p></p>",
                        "<p><em>{Write you answer here}  </em></p>"
                      ]
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "content": {
                      "type": "Text",
                      "format": "html",
                      "text": [
                        "<p><strong>Create a Diagram tile to sort your factors, and add one input block for each factor. If factors are really important to completing the task, move them to the left hand side of the screen. If they can be ignored (either because you have changed your mind or found a better way to incorporate that idea), move them to the right of the screen. If the factor might be important, move it to the middle. </strong></p>",
                        "<p>If you need more space, click on the small triangle on the bottom right of the tile, then drag it down and make the tile bigger.</p>",
                        "<p></p>",
                        "<p><em>{Write you answer here}  </em></p>"
                      ]
                    }
                  }
                ]
              },
              "supports": []
            },
